  "text": "The GCC optimization pass infrastructure follows this dependency chain: (1) `gcc/passes.def` is the master declarative list using macros `NEXT_PASS`, `INSERT_PASSES_AFTER`, and `TERMINATE_PASS_LIST` to define the full pass execution order \u2014 DCE appears multiple times via `NEXT_PASS(pass_dce)` and `NEXT_PASS(pass_cd_dce)`. (2) `gcc/passes.cc` implements the `pass_manager` class: its constructor (`pass_manager::pass_manager` at line 1577) includes `passes.def` to build the pass tree, `execute_pass_list` (line 2777) and `execute_pass_list_1` (line 2760) run passes sequentially, and `register_pass` (line 1499) allows plugins to inject passes. (3) `gcc/pass_manager.h` declares the `class pass_manager` (line 47) within `namespace gcc`, with pass list roots (`all_passes`, `all_lowering_passes`, etc.), the `GCC_PASS_LISTS` macro, and member pointers auto-generated from `pass-instances.def`. (4) `gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc` implements concrete GIMPLE DCE: `class pass_dce` (line 2082) extends `pass_dce_base` (line 2051) which extends `gimple_opt_pass`; `make_pass_dce` (line 2101) is the factory; `perform_tree_ssa_dce` (line 1953) does the actual dead code elimination. (5) `gcc/tree-pass.h` defines the entire pass type hierarchy: `struct pass_data` (line 40), `class opt_pass` (line 73) with virtual `gate`/`execute` methods, subclasses `gimple_opt_pass` (line 116), `rtl_opt_pass` (line 126), `ipa_opt_pass_d` (line 141), `simple_ipa_opt_pass` (line 197), `struct register_pass_info` (line 335), and declares all `make_pass_*` factory functions and `execute_pass_list`/`execute_one_pass` entry points.",
